 path←GetTatinRootSpace targetSpace;root
⍝ `targetSpace` is where the link to a package it going to be created: `#` or `⎕SE`.\\
⍝ It may be just `#` or `⎕SE` but can also be '#.Nested.Hirarchy' or just `⎕THIS` depending on circumstances
⍝ That rules whether we return (`#.{ROOT_PATH}_tatin` or `⎕SE.{ROOT_PATH}._tatin`.
 root←{0=≢⍵:'_tatin' ⋄ ⍵,'._tatin'}ROOT_PATH
 path←root Reg.CreateNamespace targetSpace
⍝Done
